lass=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=hansle>hansle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 9:51:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2041.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> need input on hybrid hunter/shadowzerker</span><hr size=1> what is you were to make a hunter with concentration in stealth, axe and left axe, and charm without any points into bow?  then you could charm mobs int he frontier to put on the people you want to take and then beat them up with the moves in axe and left axe.  would this work?  do you think it would be effective?  how do shadowzerkers perform in RvR?  thanks in advance <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usneekeerz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sneekeerz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 10:16:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2041.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: need input on hybrid hunter/shadowzerker</span><hr size=1> Stealth<br>Spear<br>Beastcraft<br><br>IMO, a hunter with this build will outperform an Assassin in melee.<br><br>Advatages:<br>-Spears do massive damage, about 200 a pop from a yellow hunter to my 44 Infiltartor. <br>-Studded leather<br>-Self dex and quick buff.<br>-A pet<br>-Escape spell<br>-Chain gun bow, although your bow wont do much dmg with no spec, it will still do alot. Will kill off runners most of the time.<br><br>Disadvantage:<br>-No poison<br>-No safe fall<br>-No climbing<br>-No CS opener <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=hansle>hansle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 10:45:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2041.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: need input on hybrid hunter/shadowzerker</span><hr size=1> oops i didn't do my research far enough i see that hunters can't use axe/left axe. out the shadowzerker or hybrid hunter which do u think would be the most fun to play and also the most lethal. (keep in mind i like to hunt people alot and have been to known to follow prey for 30 minutes so i don't mind waiting for the right moment)  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufandangodarkdance.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fandango Darkdance</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 1:11:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2041.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: need input on hybrid hunter/shadowzerker</span><hr size=1> If it were me I would go hunter, I had the missfortune of deleting mine and regret it every time I log on. The shadowblade simply does not do enough damage or have the means to escape. Where as a hunter can do nice damage and live to tell about it. The following is the template I would use and is the one my archer friends are using and seems to work great for them, all listed will be base skill.<br><br>Stealth 37<br>Beast 35<br>Bow 40<br>Spear 40<br><br>We are close to having our full group ready to rock. Wich will be 4 or 5 archers depending on ones wife and 3 shadow blades. In the event that one Archer can't make it our battle shaman* will buff and rest inside the port in fort.<br><br>Aug/Cave specd Shaman. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufandangodarkdance.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fandango Darkdance</A> at: 2/6/02 1:12:31 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaxterixenobelix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Axterix EnObelix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 3:55:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2041.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: need input on hybrid hunter/shadowzerker</span><hr size=1> If you want melee only, the shadow'berk owns the hunter.  Hunter buffs weren't enough before they got reduced.  They aren't enough after.<br><br>However, the ability for the hunter to throw bow into the mix is big.  After all, why walk up to the target at melee range if you can shoot them at range for more damage at a higher rate of attack? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulisboa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lisboa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 4:07:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2041.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: need input on hybrid hunter/shadowzerker</span><hr size=1> Play your hunter as straight melee through level 24-28 with zero points on bow.  Then you have autotrained your bow to 6 or higher.  Most hunters I group with just stand around and wait for thanes or the healer to pull, and melee the whole time anyway.  <br><br>Make your hunter a dwarf or norseman and he'll be as good or better at melee and taking hits than the typical SB.  But use the spear, the styles are supposedly better and your buffs go to dex, not strength, unless you have some twink two handers lying around. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulisboa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lisboa</A> at: 2/6/02 4:08:54 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufandangodarkdance.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fandango Darkdance</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 4:54:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2041.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: need input on hybrid hunter/shadowzerker</span><hr size=1> I agree with Lisboa, on the race. While I prefer the Kolbold for such things as swiming under the h20 surface making detection harder and such. I would recomend a dwarf, I would not recomend the norse tho. Although must say that with spear and bow having damage from dex as a modifier and obvious reasons for a kolby I wouldnt count them out either. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showPrevMessage?topicID=2041.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showNextMessage?topicID=2041.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2041.topic&index=6><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/f